    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-03-23T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-03-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="790"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d790">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.00/1355</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Sweden</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_MIN1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Morris</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Stockholm</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-03-23">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 23, 1918</hi>
                        </date>. <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 4.56 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1755. Swedish press reports from Petrograd demobilization on front completed.
                    Yesterday last military organizations dissolved. Reports labor council at
                    Simferopol has advised Smolny as to establishment of independent Taurida
                    republic comprising whole of Crimea and has submitted list of delegates to
                    Council of People’s Commissioners of new republic.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_MIN1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Morris</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
